Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category, as the paper discusses the implementation of a Trusted Execution Environment (TEE) and the evaluation of its performance. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely, as the paper discusses the performance of SGX-enabled nodes. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category, as the paper discusses the implementation of enclaves inside the CPU. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category, as the paper discusses the porting of legacy code to run inside an SGX enclave. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is a possible category, as the paper discusses the limitations introduced by running code inside an SGX enclave.
